column1: BALANCING RESERVES IN THE BPA CONTROL AREA (Balancing Authority Area)
Beginning 1/1/2012, at 5-min increments, updated daily
This data pertains to Balancing Reserves in the BPA Control Area.
Balancing reserves are defined as the amount of generation adjustment available to offset changes in load and deviations
from forecasted generation schedules. INC reserves adjust for generators that undergenerate or when load increases
and DEC reserves make up for generators that over-generate or when load decreases. The tabular data below provides
a 5-minute history of balancing reserves available and how they are deployed in the BPA control area.
